The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Sunday, February 02, 2003 				 Complaint to poll chief
 A STAFF REPORTER																								Trinamul Congress legislator Sovandeb Chattopadhayay on Saturday complained about the CPMs rampant malpractices and scientific rigging during elections at an all-party meet convened by Chief Election Commissioner J.M. Lyngdoh.																								 The meeting was held to discuss means to conduct fair polls and was attended by Left Front chairman Biman Bose and other MLAs.																								Polls in Bengal have become a farce as the CPM manipulate voters lists and intimidate supporters of opponent parties, Chattopadhyay told Lyngdoh, who was on a days visit to the city to inaugurate the election office inside Jessop Building.																								Diamond display																								Expressions 2003, an exclusive collection of diamonds showcasing the Asmi range of jewellery, is on display in all the city showrooms of Senco Gold Museum from 11 am to 8 pm. The display will continue till February 4.																								nClarification: The Saturday edition of Metro announced a sarod recital by Ustad Ali Akbar Khan, scheduled for February 2 at Calcutta Club. The show had been cancelled. 
